<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      i18n:domain="voteit.core">
<body>

<p>You've just received a meeting entry ticket to <b>${meeting.title}</b>.
<tal:sender:profile condition="sender_profile">It was sent to you by <b>${sender_profile.title}</b>.</tal:sender:profile>
</p>

<tal:message condition="message">
<p>${message}</p>
</tal:message>

<p>The link below grant you the following permissions within the meeting:
<ul>
    <li tal:repeat="role roles" tal:content="role">Role</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
To access this meeting use the link below:<br/>
<a tal:attributes="href access_link"
   tal:content="access_link">link</a>
</p>
<h3>Contact</h3>
<p>
The contact person for this meeting is 
<b>${meeting.get_field_value('meeting_mail_name')}</b>
<tal:mail condition="contact_mail">
and can be reached on <a href="mailto:${contact_mail}">${contact_mail}</a>
</tal:mail>
</p>
<h3>No clue what this is about or you just want to know more?</h3>
<p>
VoteIT is a meeting system created by a group of Swedish Non-profit NGOs.
<a href="http://www.voteit.se">http://www.VoteIT.se</a>
</p>
<h3>Need the manual?</h3>
<p>
All manuals are here: <a href="http://manual.voteit.se">http://manual.VoteIT.se</a>
</p>
<p>
Note that this message doesn't mean that you're subscribed to a mailing list or similar.
You're probably receiving it since you're a member of an organisaiton.
</p>
</body>
</html>
